Sort Daily Transaction Data using Merge Sort
A financial analytics system in Chennai collects thousands of transaction values daily. Before generating reports, the system must sort all transaction values efficiently without using built-in sorting functions.

Input format :
First line: integer n (size of array)
Second line: n space-separated integers
Output format :
First line: sorted array

Code constraints :
1 <= n <= 5 * 10^4
-5 * 10^4 <= nums[i] <= 5 * 10^4
Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
4  
5 2 3 1
Output 1 :
1 2 3 5
Input 2 :
5
10 -2 7 3 0
Output 2 :
-2 0 3 7 10


Solution:


// You are using GCC
#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main() {

    int n;
    cin >> n;

    vector<int> arr(n);

    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> arr[i];
    }

    for(int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {

        for(int j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++) {

            if(arr[j] > arr[j + 1]) {
                swap(arr[j], arr[j + 1]);
            }
        }
    }

    for(int x : arr) {
        cout << x << " ";
    }

    return 0;
}
